3. Workflow Overview
3.1 Faculty Initiated Leave Request
1.	Faculty submits the Google Form.
2.	Form data populates LeaveRequest (Columns A–I).
3.	System generates a timestamp-based token in LeaveRequest!L.
4.	Approval request is sent to Chair:
o	Look up Chair email using Department_Directory.
o	Email contains:
	Leave details (Timestamp, Requester, Dept, Position, Leave Type, From–To, Total Hours, Additional Details)
	Editable “Hours Approved” textbox
	Approve / Reject buttons (linked to token-based web app)
5.	Chair approves/rejects:
o	Record written to Chair_Approval.
o	Notification sent to Faculty, Chair.
o	If approved → Dean approval triggered.
o	If rejected → workflow ends.
6.	Dean approval:
o	Email includes request summary and Chair’s decision.
o	Dean edits hours and clicks Approve/Reject.
o	Record written to Dean_Approval.
o	Notification sent to Faculty, Chair, Dean.
o	If approved → Hospital Director approval triggered.
o	If rejected → workflow ends.
7.	Hospital Director approval:
o	Email includes full summary (Faculty request + Chair + Dean decisions)
o	Director edits hours, clicks Approve/Reject.
o	Record written to HospitalDirector_Approval.
o	Notification sent to Faculty, Chair, Dean, Director.
o	Workflow marked as Completed.
________________________________________
3.2 Chair Initiated Leave Request
1.	Chair submits leave form.
2.	Form data populates LeaveRequest.
3.	Token generated in LeaveRequest!L.
4.	Approval request sent directly to Hospital Director (Approval!B3).
5.	Director approves/rejects:
o	Record written to HospitalDirector_Approval.
o	Notifications sent to Chair, Dean, Director.
6.	Workflow marked as Completed.
________________________________________
4. Token-Based Tracking
•	Token format: LR-[YYYYMMDD]-[HHMMSS]-[Random3Letters]
•	Stored in LeaveRequest!L.
•	All approval sheets reference the token (Column D) for relational tracking.
•	Ensures accurate linking of approvals to leave request.
________________________________________
5. Email Flow
5.1 Chair Email (for Faculty-initiated request)
•	Request summary (Columns A–I)
•	Editable Hours Approved textbox
•	Approve / Reject buttons
•	On button click → triggers handleChairResponse(token, decision, hours)
________________________________________
5.2 Dean Email (after Chair approval)
•	Leave request summary
•	Chair’s decision summary
•	Editable Hours Approved textbox
•	Approve / Reject buttons
•	On button click → triggers handleDeanResponse(token, decision, hours)
________________________________________
5.3 Hospital Director Email
•	Full summary of leave request, Chair and Dean approvals
•	Editable Hours Approved textbox
•	Approve / Reject buttons
•	On button click → triggers handleDirectorResponse(token, decision, hours)
________________________________________
5.4 Final Notification
•	Sent to all relevant parties:
o	Faculty, Chair, Dean, Director
•	Includes final approval status, approved hours, and timestamps.
________________________________________
 
6. Trigger Flow Table
Trigger Name	Trigger Type	Activated When	Sheet Target	Function	Safeguards	Outcome
onLeaveRequestSubmit	installable onFormSubmit	New leave request	LeaveRequest	Generate token, send initial email	Only trigger for new entries, skip if token exists	Chair email sent / Director if Chair initiates
handleChairApproval	installable onEdit	Chair edits Column B	Chair_Approval	Record decision, timestamp, token, send Dean email if approved	Confirm sheet & column, valid token	Chair_Approval log updated, next approver notified
handleDeanApproval	installable onEdit	Dean edits Column B	Dean_Approval	Record decision, timestamp, token, send Director email if approved	Confirm sheet & column, valid token	Dean_Approval log updated, next approver notified
handleDirectorApproval	installable onEdit	Director edits Column B	HospitalDirectorApproval	Record decision, timestamp, token, send final notification	Confirm sheet & column, valid token	Director_Approval log updated, workflow completed
checkAllApprovals	time-driven	Periodic (every 10 min)	All sheets	Detect fully approved requests, mark final	Skip already processed	Trigger final notification
checkPendingApprovals	time-driven	Every 24h	All sheets	Identify pending approvals >48h, send reminder	Only unprocessed requests	Reminder emails sent
