7. Utility Functions
Function	Purpose
generateToken()	Create timestamp + random token for new requests
sendApprovalEmail(role, email, token, details)	Generate HTML email for approval with editable hours and buttons
handleChairResponse(token, decision, hours)	Record Chair approval and trigger Dean email if approved
handleDeanResponse(token, decision, hours)	Record Dean approval and trigger Director email if approved
handleDirectorResponse(token, decision, hours)	Record Director approval and trigger final notification
sendFinalNotification(token)	Notify all parties with final approval summary
logAction(actor, action, sheet, rowId)	Append audit log entry
enableAllTriggers() / disableAllTriggers()	Administrative control for debugging
________________________________________
8. Safeguards & Best Practices
1.	Installable triggers only (avoid simple onEdit / onFormSubmit)
2.	Conditional checks in every trigger (sheet, column, token validity)
3.	Centralized logging (hidden sheet or Logger) to avoid loops
4.	Single spreadsheet to reduce cross-file delays and authorization issues
5.	Modular scripts:
o	Code.gs → main logic
o	EmailUtils.gs → email templates
o	ApprovalProcessing.gs → handle approval updates
o	HTML folder → email templates
6.	Time-based triggers for backups or reminders (5–10 min for critical, 24h for reminders)
7.	Token-based relational tracking ensures all approval logs are linked to the original request
8.	Audit trail in approval sheets ensures traceability and accountability
